  "voiceover": "Here's the one detail skeptics can't explain away. All four Gospels say the first witnesses to the empty tomb were women. But in the first century, a woman's testimony wasn't even accepted in a court of law. So if you were inventing a story to convince that society, you'd never hand the most important moment to witnesses no one would believe — you'd put respected men there. But the Gospel writers kept the embarrassing detail anyway. Why? Because they weren't crafting propaganda — they were reporting what actually happened. Awkward, unhelpful details like this aren't how you invent a legend. They're the fingerprint of history.",
